</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({3},{3}\right)}</m></li><li><image width="52%"  pi:generated="problems/images/ce57f22d1398ba9aade4fc8356f26f98.png" />
</li></ul></p><p>The form of a parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={a}{\left({x}-{h}\right)}^{{2}}+{k}</m>. Because this parabola is <m>\displaystyle{y}={6}{\left({x}-{3}\right)}^{{2}}+{3}</m>, which can be written <m>\displaystyle{y}={6}{\left({x}-{\left({3}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({3}\right)}</m> we know the following.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{h}={3}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{k}={3}</m>. Thus the vertex is <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>
<p>To graph the parabola we can use the vertex and another convenient point. One convenient point is at <m>\displaystyle{x}={3}+{1}={4}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}{\left({4}-{\left({3}\right)}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={6}{\left({1}\right)}^{{2}}+{\left({3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={6}+{\left({3}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle={9}</m>.</p>
<p>We use <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{9}\right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
